<!--
    Foreground-service notification icon.

    Framework drawables in the `android` namespace
    (e.g. `android.R.drawable.ic_dialog_info`) are not part of the public
    contract for ongoing notifications. On API 34+/36 the system can reject
    a foreground-service notification with a framework-namespaced small icon
    (`RemoteServiceException: Bad notification for startForeground`), which
    kills the whole process — exactly the "app crashes on Connect" symptom
    we hit after fresh install.

    Status-bar small icons are masked to a single tint by the system from
    API 21 onward, so we ship a plain white silhouette and let the platform
    recolour it.

    The glyph mirrors the in-app Bluetooth vector in MainScreen.
-->
